</div> 
<p><strong>Silver Mirrorshield</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Medium Shields" href="/Medium+Shields">Medium Shield</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Silver Mirrorshield</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Shields" href="/Shields">Shield</a> that scales primarily with Strength and Intelligence. It is a very good shield for mages and spellblades and highly resistant to magic. <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Medium Shields" href="/Medium+Shields" target="">Medium Shields</a>&nbsp;feature a good balance between defense and weight, which is great for most situations in combat. Although it may not be as light as a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Small Shields" href="/Small+Shields">Small Shield</a> which is good for agility and parrying, a Medium Shield works better at reducing damage and blocking.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Shield of radiant silver, festooned with amber and carried by Loretta, Knight of the Haligtree.<br></em></p> 
 <p><em>The shape is said to imitate that of a sacred drop of dew, which inspired the absurd rumor that Loretta herself was an Albinauric.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Silver Mirrorshield in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The <strong>Silver Mirrorshield</strong>&nbsp;Shield can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Found in the northern area of <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consecrated Snowfield" href="/Consecrated+Snowfield">Consecrated Snowfield</a>, inside the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Apostate Derelict" href="/Apostate+Derelict" target="">Apostate Derelict</a> destroyed church.<br>[<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=2992&amp;lat=-57.592188&amp;lng=132.02672&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=2992&amp;lat=-57.592188&amp;lng=132.02672&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Silver Mirrorshield Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Shield&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: No Skill</li> 
 <li>This&nbsp;shield&nbsp;cannot be infused with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value: <img style="width: 18px; height: 18px;" title="item_value_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_value_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px.png" alt="item value icon elden ring wiki guide 18px" width="18" height="18">100</li> 
 <li>You can use your weapon skill without having to unequip the shield first.</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Silver Mirrorshield Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a> page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></p> 
<p>This upgrade can be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a> or boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
